---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Documentation - URL Shortener API"
  description="Complete documentation for setting up and using the self-hosted URL shortener"
>
  <main class="docs">
    <div class="container">
      <aside class="sidebar">
        <nav class="docs-nav">
          <h3>Documentation</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="#quick-start">Quick Start</a></li>
            <li><a href="#getting-license">Getting a License</a></li>
            <li><a href="#configuration">Configuration</a></li>
            <li><a href="#api-endpoints">API Endpoints</a></li>
            <li><a href="#usage-examples">Usage Examples</a></li>
            <li><a href="#features">Features</a></li>
            <li><a href="#click-tracking">Click Tracking</a></li>
            <li><a href="#custom-deployment">Custom Deployment</a></li>
          </ul>
        </nav>
      </aside>

      <article class="docs-content">
        <h1>Documentation</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          Complete guide to deploying and using your self-hosted URL shortener with A/B testing capabilities.
        </p>

        <section id="quick-start">
          <h2>Quick Start with Docker</h2>
          <p>
            The easiest way to run the URL shortener is using Docker. You'll need a valid license key to get started.
          </p>

          <div class="code-block">
            <pre><code>docker run -d \
  -e LICENSE_KEY=your-license-key \
  -p 8080:3000 \
  -v $(pwd)/data:/data \
  ghcr.io/dmancevo/url-shortener:latest</code></pre>
          </div>

          <div class="info-box">
            <strong>Note:</strong> The server requires a valid license key to run. See the section below on how to get your license.
          </div>
        </section>

        <section id="getting-license">
          <h2>Getting a License Key</h2>
          <p>
            To use the URL shortener, you need a valid license key. Visit
            <a href="https://www.url-shortener-api.com">www.url-shortener-api.com</a> to purchase a license.
            Once you have your license key, set it via the <code>LICENSE_KEY</code> environment variable.
          </p>

          <h3>Getting Your API Key</h3>
          <p>
            When the server starts, it automatically generates a unique API key and displays it in the logs:
          </p>

          <div class="code-block">
            <pre><code># View the logs to get your API key
docker logs &lt;container-id&gt;</code></pre>
          </div>

          <p>You'll see output like:</p>

          <div class="code-block">
            <pre><code>================================================================================
================================================================================
                         API KEY GENERATED
================================================================================

    AbCdEfGh1234567890XyZaBcDeFgHi

    Include this key in the 'X-API-Key' header for all API requests.
    Redirects (GET /:code) do not require authentication.
================================================================================
================================================================================</code></pre>
          </div>

          <div class="warning-box">
            <strong>Important:</strong> Copy this API key immediately! You'll need it for all API requests (except redirects).
          </div>
        </section>

        <section id="configuration">
          <h2>Configuration</h2>
          <p>Customize the server using environment variables:</p>

          <div class="code-block">
            <pre><code>docker run -d \
  -e LICENSE_KEY=your-license-key \
  -e HOST=0.0.0.0 \
  -e PORT=3000 \
  -e CACHE_CAPACITY=1000 \
  -e PARTITION_COUNT=10 \
  -e STORAGE_PATH=/data/urls.json \
  -e CLICK_TRACKING_PATH=/data/clicks.jsonl \
  -p 8080:3000 \
  -v $(pwd)/data:/data \
  ghcr.io/dmancevo/url-shortener:latest</code></pre>
          </div>

          <h3>Environment Variables</h3>
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Variable</th>
                <th>Description</th>
                <th>Default</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><code>LICENSE_KEY</code></td>
                <td>License key (required)</td>
                <td>None</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>HOST</code></td>
                <td>Server host</td>
                <td><code>0.0.0.0</code></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>PORT</code></td>
                <td>Server port</td>
                <td><code>3000</code></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>CACHE_CAPACITY</code></td>
                <td>Max entries in LRU cache</td>
                <td><code>1000</code></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>PARTITION_COUNT</code></td>
                <td>Number of storage partitions</td>
                <td><code>10</code></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>STORAGE_PATH</code></td>
                <td>Path to JSON storage file</td>
                <td><code>./data/urls.json</code></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>CLICK_TRACKING_PATH</code></td>
                <td>Path to click tracking file (optional)</td>
                <td>None</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </section>

        <section id="api-endpoints">
          <h2>API Endpoints</h2>
          <p>All endpoints except <code>GET /:code</code> require the <code>X-API-Key</code> header for authentication.</p>

          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Method</th>
                <th>Endpoint</th>
                <th>Auth Required</th>
                <th>Description</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><code>POST</code></td>
                <td><code>/shorten</code></td>
                <td>Yes</td>
                <td>Create a short URL</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>GET</code></td>
                <td><code>/:code</code></td>
                <td>No</td>
                <td>Redirect to target URL</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>PUT</code></td>
                <td><code>/:code</code></td>
                <td>Yes</td>
                <td>Update a short URL</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>DELETE</code></td>
                <td><code>/:code</code></td>
                <td>Yes</td>
                <td>Delete a short URL</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>POST</code></td>
                <td><code>/api/codes-by-url</code></td>
                <td>Yes</td>
                <td>Find short codes by URL</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>POST</code></td>
                <td><code>/api/codes-by-tag</code></td>
                <td>Yes</td>
                <td>Find short codes by tag</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>GET</code></td>
                <td><code>/api/stats</code></td>
                <td>Yes</td>
                <td>Get cache statistics</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </section>

        <section id="usage-examples">
          <h2>Usage Examples</h2>
          <p>Replace <code>YOUR_API_KEY_HERE</code> with the API key displayed when you started the server.</p>

          <h3>Basic URL Shortening</h3>
          <p>Create a short URL:</p>
          <div class="code-block">
            <pre><code>curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/shorten \
  -H "X-API-Key: YOUR_API_KEY_HERE" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"url": "https://example.com/very/long/url"}'</code></pre>
          </div>

          <p>Response:</p>
          <div class="code-block">
            <pre><code>{
  "short_code": "abc12345",
  "url": "https://example.com/very/long/url"
}</code></pre>
          </div>

          <h3>URL with Tags</h3>
          <p>Organize URLs with tags:</p>
          <div class="code-block">
            <pre><code>curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/shorten \
  -H "X-API-Key: YOUR_API_KEY_HERE" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "url": "https://example.com/landing-page",
    "tag": "marketing-campaign"
  }'</code></pre>
          </div>

          <h3>URL with Expiration</h3>
          <p>Create temporary URLs that automatically expire:</p>
          <div class="code-block">
            <pre><code>curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/shorten \
  -H "X-API-Key: YOUR_API_KEY_HERE" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "url": "https://example.com/temporary-sale",
    "expires_in": "2h"
  }'</code></pre>
          </div>
          <p>Expiration formats: <code>"5m"</code> (5 minutes), <code>"2h"</code> (2 hours), <code>"3d"</code> (3 days)</p>

          <h3>A/B Testing</h3>
          <p>Split traffic between multiple URLs:</p>
          <div class="code-block">
            <pre><code>curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/shorten \
  -H "X-API-Key: YOUR_API_KEY_HERE" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "urls": [
      {"url": "https://example.com/variant-a", "weight": 0.5},
      {"url": "https://example.com/variant-b", "weight": 0.5}
    ]
  }'</code></pre>
          </div>
          <div class="info-box">
            <strong>Note:</strong> Weights must sum to 1.0. The same visitor (identified by IP address) will always see the same variant.
          </div>

          <h3>Find Short Codes by Tag</h3>
          <div class="code-block">
            <pre><code>curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/codes-by-tag \
  -H "X-API-Key: YOUR_API_KEY_HERE" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"tag": "marketing-campaign"}'</code></pre>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section id="features">
          <h2>Features</h2>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li><strong>A/B Testing:</strong> Split traffic between multiple URLs with configurable weights</li>
            <li><strong>Deterministic Routing:</strong> Same visitor always sees the same variant (based on IP hash)</li>
            <li><strong>URL Expiration:</strong> Set automatic expiration times for temporary links</li>
            <li><strong>Tag Support:</strong> Organize and categorize short URLs with optional tags</li>
            <li><strong>Click Tracking (Optional):</strong> Privacy-conscious analytics with IP truncation</li>
            <li><strong>High Performance:</strong> LRU cache with partitioned storage for millions of URLs</li>
            <li><strong>API Key Authentication:</strong> Secure API endpoints with automatic key generation</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="click-tracking">
          <h2>Click Tracking (Optional)</h2>
          <p>To enable click tracking, add the <code>CLICK_TRACKING_PATH</code> environment variable:</p>
          <div class="code-block">
            <pre><code>docker run -d \
  -e LICENSE_KEY=your-license-key \
  -e CLICK_TRACKING_PATH=/data/clicks.jsonl \
  -p 8080:3000 \
  -v $(pwd)/data:/data \
  ghcr.io/dmancevo/url-shortener:latest</code></pre>
          </div>

          <p>Click data is stored in JSONL format with privacy protections:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>IP truncation (last 2 octets removed for IPv4)</li>
            <li>Timestamp</li>
            <li>Browser and OS information</li>
            <li>Device category</li>
            <li>Short code accessed</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="warning-box">
            <h4>GDPR Considerations</h4>
            <p>
              If you serve users in the EU/EEA and enable click tracking, GDPR may apply.
              Even with IP truncation, the collected data may be considered personal data under GDPR.
              Consider implementing:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>A privacy policy disclosing what data is collected and why</li>
              <li>A data retention policy</li>
              <li>A legal basis for processing (legitimate interest or consent)</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              Click tracking is most appropriate for internal/corporate use, personal projects,
              or when users are aware of the analytics.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section id="custom-deployment">
          <h2>Custom Deployment</h2>
          <p>Create custom deployments by extending the base image:</p>
          <div class="code-block">
            <pre><code>FROM ghcr.io/dmancevo/url-shortener:latest

# Set default environment variables
ENV HOST=0.0.0.0
ENV PORT=3000
ENV CACHE_CAPACITY=2000
ENV PARTITION_COUNT=20

# Expose the port
EXPOSE 3000</code></pre>
          </div>

          <p>Build and run:</p>
          <div class="code-block">
            <pre><code>docker build -t my-url-shortener .
docker run -d \
  -e LICENSE_KEY=your-license-key \
  -p 8080:3000 \
  -v $(pwd)/data:/data \
  my-url-shortener</code></pre>
          </div>
        </section>

        <div class="docs-footer">
          <p>Need help? Visit our <a href="https://github.com/dmancevo/url-shortener">GitHub repository</a> or check the community forums.</p>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .docs {
    padding: 2rem 0;
  }

  .docs .container {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 250px 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    max-width: 1400px;
  }

  .sidebar {
    position: sticky;
    top: 2rem;
    height: fit-content;
  }

  .docs-nav h3 {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--secondary);
  }

  .docs-nav ul {
    list-style: none;
  }

  .docs-nav li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .docs-nav a {
    color: var(--text-light);
    display: block;
    padding: 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 0.25rem;
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }

  .docs-nav a:hover {
    color: var(--primary);
    background: var(--bg-alt);
  }

  .docs-content {
    max-width: 900px;
  }

  .docs-content h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--secondary);
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--text-light);
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .docs-content section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .docs-content h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--secondary);
    padding-top: 1rem;
    border-top: 2px solid var(--border);
  }

  .docs-content h3 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin: 2rem 0 1rem;
    color: var(--secondary);
  }

  .docs-content h4 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0 0.75rem;
    color: var(--secondary);
  }

  .docs-content p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .docs-content ul:not(.feature-list) {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  .docs-content li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .code-block {
    background: var(--secondary);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    overflow-x: auto;
  }

  .code-block pre {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .code-block code {
    color: #e2e8f0;
    font-family: 'Monaco', 'Courier New', monospace;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  code {
    background: var(--bg-alt);
    padding: 0.2rem 0.4rem;
    border-radius: 0.25rem;
    font-family: 'Monaco', 'Courier New', monospace;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--primary);
  }

  .code-block code {
    background: transparent;
    padding: 0;
    color: #e2e8f0;
  }

  table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    background: white;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  thead {
    background: var(--bg-alt);
  }

  th {
    padding: 1rem;
    text-align: left;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--secondary);
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border);
  }

  td {
    padding: 1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  tbody tr:last-child td {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  tbody tr:hover {
    background: var(--bg-alt);
  }

  .info-box {
    background: #eff6ff;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--primary);
    padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    border-radius: 0.25rem;
  }

  .info-box strong {
    color: var(--primary);
  }

  .warning-box {
    background: #fef3c7;
    border-left: 4px solid #f59e0b;
    padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    border-radius: 0.25rem;
  }

  .warning-box strong {
    color: #d97706;
  }

  .warning-box h4 {
    color: #d97706;
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .feature-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .feature-list li {
    padding: 0.75rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .feature-list li:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .docs-footer {
    margin-top: 4rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 2px solid var(--border);
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--text-light);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .docs .container {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2rem;
    }

    .sidebar {
      position: static;
      background: var(--bg-alt);
      padding: 1rem;
      border-radius: 0.5rem;
    }

    .docs-content h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .docs-content h2 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }

    .code-block {
      padding: 1rem;
    }

    .code-block code {
      font-size: 0.75rem;
    }

    table {
      font-size: 0.875rem;
    }

    th, td {
      padding: 0.75rem 0.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
